<ContentPage
  title="The Institution"
  description="Why Fula Devi Memorial Sewa Sansthan exists, the principles that guide its decisions, and the character it seeks to uphold."
>
  <p>Every institution is shaped by the decisions it makes.</p>
  <p>Those decisions are guided by the principles behind them.</p>
  <p>
    Fula Devi Memorial Sewa Sansthan exists to ensure that every act of service
    remains faithful to those principles.
  </p>

  <h2>Why We Exist</h2>
  <p>Kindness is often personal.</p>
  <p>An institution can give it continuity.</p>
  <p>
    It allows acts of kindness to become lasting commitments rather than
    isolated moments.
  </p>

  <h2>What Guides Our Work</h2>
  <p>Our work is guided by four principles.</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Every act of service should preserve the dignity of every person.</li>
    <li>Quiet work matters more than recognition.</li>
    <li>Consistency matters more than size.</li>
    <li>Responsibility is measured by what is sustained over time.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Our Character</h2>
  <p>We believe institutions earn trust slowly.</p>
  <p>
    That trust is built through honesty, consistency, and work that speaks for
    itself.
  </p>

  <h2>How We Work</h2>
  <p>We focus on practical service.</p>
  <p>We begin with what is possible today and build patiently over time.</p>

  <p>Goodness is not something to admire.</p>
  <p>It is something to continue.</p>
</ContentPage>
